50|$|In 2001, the United Kingdom Food Standards Agency (FSA) {{found in}} tests of various sauces {{including}} soy <b>sauces</b> <b>that</b> some 22% of samples contained a chemical carcinogen called 3-MCPD at levels considerably {{higher than those}} deemed safe by the European Union as well as 1,3-DCP its derivative.|$|R
